Address.name: 2206 25a Street Sw
Address.property_info: Welcome to this open concept home total of four bedrooms, catering to the modern family’s needs. Builtin 2006, this home went through a major renovation in 2023 with new paint, new flooring (both hardwoodand carpet), new furnace and new water tank to increase energy efficiency. The new kitchen was rebuilt toinclude features of a modern kitchen with a suite of digital Samsung appliances, induction cooktop, potfiller, garburator and more. The kitchen also showcases custom cabinetry with added Lazy Susanorganizers and Legra glass box pantry drawers. The large kitchen island has beautiful quartz waterfallcountertops containing extra cabinets to store seasonal household items. Three full washrooms wereupgraded with matching cabinets and countertops, new sink and faucets. All washrooms contain newtoilet fixtures. Master bathroom was upgraded with all necessities of a modern bathroom with his/hervanities, and built in laundry baskets. This prime location is just steps away from parks (children and dogs) , closed to school, easy access to downtown by car and/or public transits. You will also appreciate the convivence of nearby retail options, local shops cafes, and community recreation center in surrounding communities that will add variety toyour social activities. In summary, this property offers a fantastic blend of practicality, style and location,making it an ideal choice for those seeking a modern and accommodating residence in theheart of Richmond. Whether you’re looking for a space of convenience or a desirableneighborhood setting, this home has it all. Don’t miss the opportunity to make it yours andexperience the best of inner-city living. Address.property_info: Step inside 80 Carrington Plaza, experience comfort in this meticulously designed 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom unit on the ground floor. This functional floor plan maximizes space, offering a seamless blend of style and practicality. Unleash your inner chef in the spacious kitchen, a rare find in units of this kind. Two-toned cabinets, sleek chevron backsplash, and upgraded light fixtures create a contemporary and inviting atmosphere. Every detail has been thoughtfully chosen to enhance your comfort and style. Experience the convenience of a large gated patio, providing a private outdoor space and a separate entrance to your parking stall right out front. Perfect for enjoying the fresh air or entertaining guests. Nestled in the up-and-coming neighbourhood of Carrington in NW Calgary, this unit is surrounded by amenities and poised for even more growth. Address.name: 105, 2727 28 Avenue Se
Address.property_info: Beautiful one bedroom condo built by Jayman. Steps to one of the nicest ridges in Calgary with incredible views of the Rockies and downtown Calgary! Shows like new and shines with upgrades. Almost 9 foot ceilings, big windows and the patio doors bring in loads of natural light. The kitchen has espresso coloured kitchen cabinets, black quartz countertops and SS appliances. The breakfast bar is huge and acts like a 4 person kitchen table. The main living area has warm cork flooring & updated paint. Off the kitchen there is a builtin desk & shelving unit~ great for the home office. There is a pantry in the kitchen and a coat closet at the front door. The main bathroom is oversized as it contains not only the 4 pce bath but the stacker washer/dryer as well. The Master bedroom is large and has a good sized walkin closet. From the Master you can actually see Calgarys skyline! Off the living room there are sliding glass doors that go out to a good sized covered patio~ great for relaxing after work and the summer BBQ's. Serene setting for a condo complex~ just off the ridge and backing onto a huge greenspace. The back courtyard is awesome for entertaining. Easy walk to Valleyview Park which has a splash park for the kids, a large volleyball area, picnic tables & playground. There are miles of walking paths which run parallel to the ridge so you get full views of the Rockies/downtown the entire time. Underground heated parking is titled (#181) plus there is a storage cage at the back of the stall as well. The bike storage is handy and included in your condo fees which are reasonable at $343 a month. There are solar panels on the roof which are to help offset the overall electrical load here. Board approval for pets~ 1 dog or cat with a weight restriction as well (id:27)

Address.name: 411, 615 6 Avenue Se
Address.property_info: OPEN HOUSE - Sunday, Feb 25th from 11am-3pm. Prepare to be awestruck! Nestled on the 4th floor, this exquisite 2 bed/2 bath residence offers not only breathtaking vistas but also unparalleled seclusion. Crafted by the renowned Cecconi Simone, the design is a testament to luxury living. Step inside to discover an open floor plan, featuring a chef's kitchen equipped with top-of-the-line stainless steel appliances including a ceramic cooktop and wall oven. Adorned with quartz countertops and a grand centre island, the kitchen seamlessly flows into the inviting living room, where floor-to-ceiling windows bathe the space in natural light. Venture outside to the expansive covered balcony and indulge in panoramic views of downtown Calgary, while relishing the perfect blend of indoor-outdoor living. Retreat to the primary bedroom, adorned with oversized windows, and unwind in the 3-piece ensuite bathroom boasting quartz countertops and elegant tiled flooring. A second bedroom, complete with ample closet space, and a well-appointed 4-piece bathroom complete the living quarters. The Verve offers a plethora of amenities including a rooftop patio, owners lounge/social room, conference room, private gym, and an observation deck on the 25th floor, promising unparalleled luxury living in the heart of East Village. With convenient access to the C-train and major attractions like the Stampede grounds and the Calgary Zoo, this is an opportunity not to be missed! See multimedia button for a video or call to book your showing! (id:27)
